## Replace one pattern with one replacement (khong phan biet letters va words)

animal_bite <- animal_bite %>% mutate(color=stringr::str_replace(color,"BLA","BLACK"))

animal_bite <- animal_bite %>% mutate(color=stringr::str_replace(color,"BLACKCKCKCKCK","BLACK"))

animal_bite <- animal_bite %>% mutate(color=stringr::str_replace(color,"BLACKCK","BLACK"))

## Replace multiple patterns with one replacement 

a <- c("BRO|BRN")

library(stringr)
animal_bite$color <- str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, a,"BROWN")

animal_bite$color <- animal_bite$color %>% str_replace("BROWNWN","BROWN")

animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, c("WHT" = "WHITE", "WHIT" = "WHITE", "BL\\s" = "BLUE"))

animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, "WHITEE","WHITE")

### Replace multiple patterns with multiple replacements

animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, c("-" = " & ", "GREY" = "GRAY", "GRY" = "GRAY", "BWN$"="BROWN", "BLCK"="BLCK", "AND"= "&"))

animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, c("ORG$" = "ORANGE", "CHOC" = "CHOCOLA", "BLU$" = "BLUE", "GRAU"="GRAY", "BL$"="BLUE", "WHITE GRAY B"= "WHITE GRAY", "//"=" ", "BLACK SIV" = "BLACK", "BRW"="BROWN"))

animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, c("LT. BROWN" = "BROWN", "BROWN0 WHITE" = "BROWN WHITE", "BL BRINDLE" = "BLUE BRINDLE", "MULTI"="MULT COLOR", "BROWN BRINDL"="BROWN BRINDLE", "BLUEBRINDLE" = "BLUE BRINDLE", "TORTI$"="TORTIE"))

animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, c("/" = " ", "BROWNNW" = "BROWN", "CHOCOLA\\s" = "CHOCOLATE", "WHITE BLACK OR"="WHITE BLACK", "BROWND"="BROWN", "BRN/" = "BROWN ", "WTE/"="WHITE "))


animal_bite$color <-str_replace_all(animal_bite$color, c("BR CREAM B" = "BROWN CREAM BLACK", "BWN WHITE"= "BROWN WHITE", "ORG BROWN" = "ORANGE BROWN", "GRAY WHITEE" ="GRAY WHITE", "GRAT WGT" ="GRAY WGT", "BROWN BROWNL" = "BROWN", "MULT"= "MULTI COLOR", "LGHT BROWN"="LIGHT BROWN", "LGT BROWN"= "LIGHT BROWN", "TRI CLR"="TRI COLOR", "N A"="NA","BLC"="BLACK", "BLUEBROWN"="BLUE BROWN","BROWNL WHITE"="BROWN WHITE", "BLUEWHITE"="BLUE WHITE", "BROWN TAB WHITE"="BROWN TAN WHITE", "FAW WHITE"="FAWN WHITE", "GINGER TAB"= "GINGER TAN","BLACK WH BROWN" = "BLACK WHITE BROWN", "WHITEIE BROWN"="WHITE BROWN"))

### Way 1:  group_by (if not recoding before)
animal_bite_species <- animal_bite %>% group_by(SpeciesIDDesc) %>% summarize(n=n(),percentage=round(n/sum(animal_bite_species$n)*100, 2))

### Way2: group_by (if not recoding before)

animal_bite_species <- animal_bite %>% 
  group_by(SpeciesIDDesc) %>% count() %>% ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(percentage = (`n` / sum(`n`))) %>% 
  arrange(percentage) %>%
  mutate(labels = scales::percent(percentage))


animal_bite_species <- animal_bite_species %>% mutate(percentage = (`n`/ sum(`n`))) %>% arrange(percentage) 

animal_bite_species$percentage <- round(animal_bite_species$percentage,2)

animal_bite_species <- animal_bite_species %>% mutate(labels =scales::percent(percentage))

animal_bite_species <- animal_bite_species %>% mutate(labels=stringr::str_replace(labels,".0",""))
animal_bite_species
ggplot(animal_bite_species, aes(x = "", y = percentage, fill = SpeciesIDDesc)) +
  geom_col(color = "black") +
  geom_text(aes(label = labels, x = 1.3),
            position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +
  coord_polar(theta = "y") + 
  theme_void()
